        <div class="blocks-container">
            <div class="block full-width-block">
                <h2>About me</h2>
                <p>Hi! I'm Rachel.</p>
                <p>I work for <a href="https://worksinprogress.co/" target="_blank">Works in Progress</a>, a magazine, and <a href="https://press.stripe.com/" target="_blank">Stripe Press</a>, a book publisher, hosting events. I also cover operations for Works in Progress, including working to launch our new print magazine (coming this autumn!).</p>
                <p>Previously, I worked on events for <a href="https://longview.org/" target="_blank">Longview Philanthropy</a>, advised the <a href="https://committees.parliament.uk/committee/158/treasury-committee/" target="_blank">Treasury Committee</a> on financial services policy, and worked a few different jobs at the <a href="https://www.bankofengland.co.uk/" target="_blank">Bank of England</a>. I studied Economics and Politics at the University of York, and have an MSc in Central Banking and Financial Regulation from the University of Warwick.</p>
                <p>I live in London, and I like hosting dinner parties, going for absurdly long walks, and playing the piano.</p>
                <p>I've signed the <a href="https://www.givingwhatwecan.org/" target="_blank">Giving What We Can</a> pledge, committing myself to giving 10% of my income to effective charity, for life. Charities I donate to include the <a href="https://www.againstmalaria.com/" target="_blank">Against Malaria Foundation</a>, <a href="https://ourworldindata.org/" target="_blank">Our World In Data</a>, the <a href="https://leadelimination.org/" target="_blank">Lead Exposure Elimination Project</a>, <a href="https://www.newincentives.org/" target="_blank">New Incentives</a>, and <a href="https://savelife.in.ua/en/" target="_blank">Come Back Alive</a>.</p>
            </div>

            <div class="block">
                <h2>My writing</h2>
                <p>I write <a href="https://accidents.substack.com/" target="_blank">Rare Accidents</a>, an infrequent substack where I review fringe theatre in London.</p>
                <p>I've reviewed shows for <a href="https://everything-theatre.co.uk/author/rachel-edwards" target="_blank">Everything Theatre</a>, <a href="https://theatreweekly.com/author/racheledwards/" target="_blank">Theatre Weekly</a>, and the <a href="https://www.thereviewshub.com/a-thousand-sons-etcetera-theatre-london/" target="_blank">Reviews Hub</a>. For older shows (2022 and back), see my <a href="https://kingdomforastage.wordpress.com/" target="_blank">archive on Wordpress</a>.</p>
                <p>I'm (very slowly) writing a play based on Shakespeare's Henry IV plays. An extract from <em>The Prince's Shadow</em> appears in <a href="https://www.waterstones.com/book/the-shakespeare-multiverse/valerie-m-fazel/louise-geddes/9780367257347" target="_blank">The Shakespeare Multiverse</a>, part of the Routledge Studies in Shakespeare series.</p>
                <p>I like poetry, particularly sonnets, and I occasionally run sonnet competitions online. Previous themes include <a href="https://accidents.substack.com/p/the-sonnet-competition-again" target="_blank">distance</a> and <a href="https://accidents.substack.com/p/the-sonnet-competition" target="_blank">salt</a>.</p>
            </div>

            <div class="block">
                <h2>Vauxhall Dances</h2>
                <p>With friends, I run semi-regular ceilidh dancing in London. We have the wonderful <a href="https://www.reeling.co.uk/" target="_blank">John Carver</a> doing the calling, it's very beginner-friendly. DM for info and tickets.</p>
            </div>

            <div class="block">
